        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 2:29PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 229 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Scotts Fork, or near Amelia Courthouse, moving northwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Amelia Courthouse around 235 PM EDT.
Morven around 255 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Angola, Earls,
Rodophil, Giles Mill, Winterham, Paineville, Maplewood, Belona,
Lodore, and Truxillo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
